ExecDesc.value: Microsoft Windows Graphics Rendering Engine BMP File Parsing Integer Overflow

EngDesc.value: A vulnerability has been discovered in the Graphics Rendering Engine (GRE) component of Microsoft Windows. Specifically this vulnerability is exposed by the Microsoft Windows GDI+ subsystem. An attacker can exploit this vulnerability by enticing a user to open a malicious BMP file, resulting in either a denial of service, or in the injection and execution of arbitrary code with the privileges of the currently logged in user.
